            "headline": "Mathematician, data scientist",
            "summary": "I'm a versatile problem solver with broad interests and an open mind, always looking forward to tackling challenging questions in applied mathematics. My journey has taken me from being a researcher in mathematical physics to a lead data scientist, and more recently, I’ve added the role of professor of mathematics to my career.\n\nAt heart, I’m a scientist driven by curiosity. My current research and professional interests include:\n\n- Mathematical statistics and geometric data analysis\n- Visualizing networks and interpreting high-dimensional data\n- Exploring applications of large language models (LLMs), with a focus on embeddings and semantic search\n- Teaching and mentoring in mathematics and statistics\n\nIn the past, I’ve explored topics such as:\n\n- Mathematical relativity and Lorentzian geometry\n- Simulating pedestrian flows in complex environments\n- Image processing\n\nI love working on interdisciplinary problems, blending theory with practical approaches to push boundaries—whether in academia, industry, or anywhere in between.",
